---

<AdminLayout
  title="Navs and Tabs"
  description="Modern navigation components with various styles and layouts"
  currentPath="interface/navs-and-tabs"
  enableComponentPreview={true}
  enableToc={true}
>
  <PageHeader {...pageConfig} />
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-10 order-1 order-md-0">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <p class="my-0">
            Bootstrap's navigation components offer flexible and responsive solutions for organizing
            content and enhancing user experience. From simple navigation bars to complex tabbed
            interfaces, these components provide various styling options and layouts to create
            intuitive navigation systems that adapt seamlessly across different screen sizes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row js-toc-content">
        <div class="col-12">
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="base-nav">Base Navigation</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The base navigation component demonstrates the fundamental structure using <code
                >nav</code
              > class. Each navigation item (<code>nav-item</code>) contains a link (<code
                >nav-link</code
              >) with optional icons for enhanced visual hierarchy. The <code>aria-current</code> attribute
              indicates the active page for accessibility.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Base Navigation with Icons"
              height="100px"
              component={basicNavExample}
              htmlCode={basicNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="available-styles">Available Styles</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Bootstrap's navigation system provides multiple styling options to create visually
              distinct and functional navigation patterns. Each style can be enhanced with icons and
              customized to match your application's design language.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="horizontal-alignment">Horizontal Alignment</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Control the horizontal positioning of navigation items using Bootstrap's
              justify-content utilities. The <code>justify-content-center</code> class centers items,
              while <code>justify-content-end</code> aligns them to the right.
            </p>

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Centered Navigation"
              height="100px"
              component={centeredNavExample}
              htmlCode={centeredNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />

            <ComponentPreview
              title="Right-Aligned Navigation"
              height="100px"
              component={rightAlignedNavExample}
              htmlCode={rightAlignedNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="vertical-alignment">Vertical Alignment</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The <code>flex-column</code> class vertically aligns the nav items, stacking them in a
              column instead of the default horizontal layout.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Vertical Alignment"
              height="250px"
              component={verticalNavExample}
              htmlCode={verticalNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="tabs">Tabs</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Tabs are created using the <code>nav</code> class with <code>nav-tabs</code>,
              providing a tabbed navigation interface where each tab can link to different content
              sections.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Tabs"
              height="150px"
              component={tabsNavExample}
              htmlCode={tabsNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="pills">Pills</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              Pills are similar to tabs but have a rounded, "pill" shape. They are created using the <code
                >nav</code
              > class with
              <code>nav-pills</code> to style the navigation items as pill-shaped buttons.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Pills"
              height="100px"
              component={pillsNavExample}
              htmlCode={pillsNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="underline">Underline</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The <code>nav-underline</code> class adds an underline style to navigation links, providing
              a clear visual indicator of the active tab or link, improving navigation clarity for users.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Underline"
              height="100px"
              component={underlineNavExample}
              htmlCode={underlineNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="fill-and-justify">Fill and justify</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The combination of <code>nav</code>, <code>nav-pills</code>, and <code>nav-fill</code>
              creates a navigation menu where the pill-styled links are evenly distributed across the
              available width, filling the container.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Nav Fill"
              height="150px"
              component={fillNavExample}
              htmlCode={fillNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />

            <p class="py-2">
              <code>nav-justified</code> makes each navigation item take up an equal width, ensuring
              that the items are spaced evenly across the entire navbar, filling the available space.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Nav Justified"
              height="200px"
              component={justifiedNavExample}
              htmlCode={justifiedNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="flex-utilities">Flex utilities</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              This code uses Bootstrap's flex utilities to create a responsive vertical and
              horizontal navigation. The
              <code>flex-column</code> class stacks the nav items vertically on smaller screens, while
              <code>flex-sm-row</code>
              changes the layout to horizontal on larger screens. Each <code>flex-sm-fill</code> class
              ensures that each nav item takes equal width in the horizontal layout, and <code
                >text-sm-center</code
              > centers the text in the items when displayed as rows.
            </p>

            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Flex Utilities"
              height="250px"
              component={responsiveNavExample}
              htmlCode={responsiveNavExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="dropdowns">Dropdowns</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              You can also add a dropdown menu within the navbar by using the <code>dropdown</code> class
              and
              <code>dropdown-toggle</code> to trigger the menu.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 id="tabs-with-dropdowns">Tabs with dropdowns</h3>
            <!-- Navs and Tabs Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Tabs with Dropdowns"
              height="200px"
              component={tabsWithDropdownExample}
              htmlCode={tabsWithDropdownExample}
              cssCode={``}
              jsCode={``}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
